I get up slowly. I don't want to fall over and smash my face into the platform. I get on the train and hang tightly onto the bar above the door.

I can see a man and a woman.

The doors close.
> interact person301
He has legs like pencils, and impossibly tight jeans, and a hairstyle.

Where did Heather go then? Why wouldn't she stick around? Hardly a spark between us, but buggering off like that when a guy passes out?
> jeans
How does he get into those jeans? Nobody has legs that thin —  and those jeans look even thinner than his legs, somehow. It must take him hours to get into those. And the hair. If I put that much effort into my appearance I would just look desparate and ridiculous.

I wonder if he's the type Heather goes for.

I wonder if he is really sad inside.

My head feels really weirdly fuzzy now. But it feels like it's aching a bit less. Maybe the brief period of unconsciousness helped the hangover.
> interact person8
There's something familiar about her. Where have I seen her before? Was she in the old office? Maybe she was in something on telly...

Did Heather just have somewhere important to be? A social media emergency?

This is London Bridge.
I could get off here. Or wait.
