This station is Balham.

I step off the train and turn right, heading for the Way Out. It's entirely automatic. 11.54am. Almost time for lunch. Maybe I'll treat myself to a can of beer as well. Hair of the dog. Might shift this hangover at last.

I'll need to call the office. I don't know what to tell them. I'm not sure if I want to go back. I could say I was really ill last night, and just woke up. I think I need a few more days to get my head together anyway. Food poisoning would be a perfect excuse.

Hey, look, it's been... interesting. I can't say it's not been fun. But I've been thinking on the way back about what Private Rod said. Or whatever his name actually is. He's made me think about a lot of things. It's going to take a take a while to work all this out.

But he's right. I need to do this on my own.
> 1
I guess what I'm trying to say is, it's probably time for us to go our separate ways. I don't think it's healthy for me to listen to you any more. And I don't want to have to keep telling you everything. I don't know you, and it's clear I don't actually need you now. I want to do my own thing. I don't want somebody watching over me the whole time, or telling me what to do. I want to figure all this out for myself.

And look, you must have your own problems anyway. You don't want me burdening you with mine as well.

The trouble is... I don't really know how to get rid of you. I have this feeling like you've been a constant presence, and there's nothing I can do to escape. I feel like you have the power to leave me at any time, but not the other way around. I need that freedom too — the freedom for me to leave you. I'm just not sure that you'd leave of your own accord otherwise. And even if you did, this needs to be my decision.

So, there is something I need to do. I don't know if this stupid or what, but it's all I can think of. I need to do this. On my own. I need to make a very big decision, and I need to ask you to do one small thing.
> 1
I'm ready. Deep breath. I can hear that it's time. It's coming. Now or never.

The two white lights of a train are approaching fast through the blackness of the tunnel. Seconds away. To my left, the stairs.

Right, quickly. Can you let me do one thing? One thing without looking.

Let me do one thing and promise you won't exert any control over my actions.

You won't look.

You won't ask.

Getting louder.

Let me do this, and let me be free.
> 1
